Authentic Mexican food and ambiance. If you dont mind Mexicans mostly from the southern states of Mexico Guerrero, Puebla mixed with Caribbean and Centro Americans this is the place to go enjoy some tacos or your fav appetizers. Beers are mad cheap make sure you order the Cubetazo(beer bucket) they give you chips and salsa or peanuts. They also do karaoke over the weekends most people here are regular and friendly if you know a word or 2 of Spanish. Mexicans may look intimidating but not really they are just respectful and dont wanna bother you but once you start up  conversation they will do everything to please you and make feel like part of the group. If somebody buys you a beer just accept it cause that person is trying to be nice to you and you dont have to give back unless you really want to. Bathrooms maybe an issue just like in any bar but they let you use the ladies room as loon as you dont make a mess when free of course. Over all place is pretty straightforward with good food and friendly staff that will make sure you have a good time so just sit back and relax. Enjoy

Authentic traditional prime location and full of true character.  Yes many see the food and the quality and the fill house with the hard working staff but what makes this establishment stand out for me is what they do when no one is looking or in this case what they do without advertising it out at least for credit. But I have seen them do this many times and it's done to help out the community and to not let GODs good food go to waste. At the end of the night all the top quality food the steak fish rice and even desserts is handed out individually to the less fortunate homeless or the needy.  Late late at night prior to their closing they wrap up food neatly and respectfully to the homeless young crowd that flood these streets.  No money is exchanged nut only thank you and blesses and this is why this place is a five out of five for me

This could possibly be the worst food I’ve ever eaten. I ordered the fajitas and what was delivered to me was the equivalent of a subpar Chinese chicken and vegetables. The sauce was what seems to be a soy base with no flavor beyond that.  The rice was dry, the beans weren’t refried, and the salad made up the majority of the meal with random raw vegetables. The salad also seemed to have a dressing on it that didn’t mix with what was expected or what was received.  Additionally, I asked for hot sauce and it was a cream sauce.  The Dominican food that was served looked delicious. However, this does not make authentic Mexican food by any means.
